We have, $$A = \left( {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 2  \cr 
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 
   3 &amp; 4  \cr 

 } } \right)$$ and $$B = \left( {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 2  \cr 
   2 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right)$$<br><br>order of A = 3 $$\times$$ 2 and order of B = 2 $$\times$$ 2<br><br>$$\because$$ Number of column of A = Number of row of B<br><br>$$\therefore$$ AB exists.<br><br>and number of column of B $$\ne$$ Number of row of A<br><br>$$\therefore$$ BA does not exist.<br><br>Hence, AB exists but BA does not exist.

Given equations are<br><br>$$x + y + z = 8$$ ....... (i)<br><br>$$x - y + 2z = 6$$ ...... (ii)<br><br>$$3x - y + 5z = k$$ ....... (iii)<br><br>Here, $$D = \left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; { - 1} &amp; 2  \cr 
   3 &amp; { - 1} &amp; 5  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = 1( - 5 + 2) - 1(5 - 6) + 1( - 1 + 3)$$<br><br>$$ =  - 3 + 1 + 2 = 0$$<br><br>$${D_1} = \left| {\matrix{
   8 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   6 &amp; { - 1} &amp; 2  \cr 
   k &amp; { - 1} &amp; 5  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = 8( - 5 + 2) - 1(30 - 2k) + 1( - 6 + k)$$<br><br>$$ =  - 24 - 30 + 2k - 6 + k$$<br><br>$$ = 3k - 60$$<br><br>$${D_2} = \left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 8 &amp; 1  \cr 
   1 &amp; 6 &amp; 2  \cr 
   3 &amp; k &amp; 5  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = 1(30 - 2k) - 8(5 - 6) + 1(k - 18)$$<br><br>$$ = 30 - 2k - 40 + 48 + k - 18 = 20 - k$$<br><br>$${D_3} = \left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 1 &amp; 8  \cr 
   1 &amp; { - 1} &amp; 6  \cr 
   3 &amp; { - 1} &amp; k  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = 1( - k + 6) - 1(k - 18) + 8( - 1 + 3)$$<br><br>$$ =  - k + 6 - k + 18 + 15 = 40 - 2k$$<br><br>For, k = 15<br><br>D = 0 and D<sub>1</sub> $$\ne$$ 0, D<sub>2</sub> $$\ne$$ 0 and D<sub>3</sub> $$\ne$$ 0.<br><br>$$\therefore$$ No solution for k = 15.<br><br>For k = 20 $$\Rightarrow$$ D<sub>1</sub> = D<sub>2</sub> = D<sub>3</sub> = 0 and D = 0<br><br>$$\therefore$$ Infinitely many solution for k = 20.<br><br>Since, D = 0<br><br>$$\therefore$$ System have no unique solution for any value of k.

We have, $$A = \left[ {\matrix{
   { - 2} &amp; 2  \cr 
   2 &amp; { - 2}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $${A^2} = A.A = \left[ {\matrix{
   { - 2} &amp; 2  \cr 
   2 &amp; { - 2}  \cr 

 } } \right]\left[ {\matrix{
   { - 2} &amp; 2  \cr 
   2 &amp; { - 2}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \left[ {\matrix{
   {4 + 4} &amp; { - 4 - 4}  \cr 
