Area of triangle whose vertices (x<sub>1</sub>, y<sub>1</sub>), (x<sub>2</sub>, y<sub>2</sub>) and (x<sub>3</sub>, y<sub>3</sub>) is<br><br>$$A = {1 \over 2}\left| {\matrix{
   {{x_1}} &amp; {{y_1}} &amp; 1  \cr 
   {{x_2}} &amp; {{y_2}} &amp; 1  \cr 
   {{x_3}} &amp; {{y_3}} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>Area of $$\Delta$$ABC<br><br>$$A\left( {{x_1},{1 \over {{x_1}}}} \right),B\left( {{x_2},{1 \over {{x_2}}}} \right),C\left( {{x_3},{1 \over {{x_3}}}} \right)$$<br><br>$$ = {1 \over 2}\left| {\matrix{
   {{x_1}} &amp; {{1 \over {{x_1}}}} &amp; 1  \cr 
   {{x_2}} &amp; {{1 \over {{x_2}}}} &amp; 1  \cr 
   {{x_3}} &amp; {{1 \over {{x_3}}}} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right| = {1 \over 2}\left| {\matrix{
   {{x_1}} &amp; {{1 \over {{x_1}}}} &amp; 1  \cr 
   {{x_2}} &amp; {{1 \over {{x_2}}}} &amp; 1  \cr 
   {{x_3}} &amp; {{1 \over {{x_3}}}} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {1 \over {2{x_1}{x_2}{x_3}}}\left| {\matrix{
   {x_1^2} &amp; 1 &amp; {{x_1}}  \cr 
   {x_2^2} &amp; 1 &amp; {{x_2}}  \cr 
   {x_3^2} &amp; 1 &amp; {{x_3}}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = \left| {{{({x_1} - {x_2})({x_2} - {x_3})({x_3} - {x_1})} \over {2{x_1}{x_2}{x_3}}}} \right|$$

We have,<br><br>$$A = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 

 } } \right]$$ and $$B = \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; { - 2}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $$AB = \left[ {\matrix{
   {1 \times 2 + ( - 1) \times ( - 1)} &amp; {1 \times 3 + ( - 1) \times ( - 2)}  \cr 
   {2 \times 2 + 3 \times ( - 1)} &amp; {2 \times 3 + 3 \times ( - 2)}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$ = \left[ {\matrix{
   3 &amp; 5  \cr 
   1 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>$$BA = \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 
   { - 1} &amp; { - 2}  \cr 

 } } \right]\left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; { - 1}  \cr 
   2 &amp; 3  \cr 

 } } \right] = \left[ {\matrix{
   8 &amp; 7  \cr 
   { - 5} &amp; { - 5}  \cr 

 } } \right]$$<br><br>Clearly, AB $$\ne$$ BA<br><br>Now, AB (A<sup>$$-$$1</sup> B<sup>$$-$$1</sup>) = AB (BA)<sup>$$-$$1</sup> [$$\because$$ (AB)<sup>$$-$$1</sup> = B<sup>$$-$$1</sup> A<sup>$$-$$1</sup>]<br><br>AB (BA)<sup>$$-$$1</sup> is a unit matrix if and only if AB = BA but AB $$\ne$$ BA. So, AB (A<sup>$$-$$1</sup> B<sup>$$-$$1</sup>) is not a unit matrix. Since, AB $$\ne$$ BA, therefore (AB)<sup>$$-$$1</sup> $$\ne$$ A<sup>$$-$$1</sup> B<sup>$$-$$1</sup>.
